 \mathbb{E}[X]=\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}kP(X=k). 
 P(X=k)=\left(\frac{5}{6}\right)^{k-1}\cdot\frac{1}{6}. 
 \mathbb{E}[X]=\frac{1}{6}\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}k\left(\frac{5}{6}\right)^{k-1} 
 \sum_{k=0}^{\infty}x^k=\frac{1}{1-x},\qquad \lvert x\rvert<1. 
 \frac{1}{(1-x)^2}=\frac{d}{dx}\left[\frac{1}{1-x}\right]=\frac{d}{dx}\left[\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}x^k\right]=\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}kx^{k-1},\qquad \lvert x\rvert<1. 
 \mathbb{E}[X]=\frac{1}{6}\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}k\left(\frac{5}{6}\right)^{k-1}=\frac{1}{6}\cdot\frac{1}{(1-\frac{5}{6})^2}=6. 
